caption: I LOVED THE FOOD!!
This was the BEST experience of my LIFE. the food was DELICIOUS!

Worst Service In The French Quarter. If you don't mind waiting 15 minutes to have your order taken then you're in luck. This is not just us but 3 other tables have all been waiting for 15 minutes.  The server is awful - basically insulted us for not knowing what the sides were...and then she pointed them out and left...said she would be back...so now it's 20 minutes later and we still haven't ordered...God forbid you ask a question about the menu here.  The food is not bad in anyway - however my order was wrong...why Lord. So I got home fries and not grits I ordered, also the fried shrimp were left off my order...everything tasted fine, it was just wrong. I can only think that's the servers fault and not the kitchens...I'm guessing it was put in wrong.  In summary, keep walking there are better places.

Very disappointing. Had always enjoyed in the past. Now, plastic plates, forks, etc. Airplane food better. Grits like rocks, overall quality awful.  Couldn't finish.  VERY SAD. I used my credit card to pay  and will dispute ASAP.
Decent little coffee and breakfast place. Some indoor and some outdoor seating. A player piano in the corner. A decent selection of breakfast items at a good price. Nice strong coffee.
gordan ramsy renovated this place didnt he

No longer the Old Coffe Pot, now its Cafė Beignet.  Major let down.  Caffeteria style food, service is poor, its 50F raining, doors all open, breezy and cold.  Loud player piano, crawfish omelette smelt/tasted bad, coffee luke warm.  1-Star for being open at 8am and beignets were good.  Best food in NOLA.  Great service, see JoJo and the rest of the servers for a true New Orleans experience.   Chicken biscuit Benedict is crazy good as well as the best gumbo anywhere.
Great little place! Great service! Awesome atmosphere! Try the Calas and grits!
Great breakfast and beignets!
OMG the best beignets we had in NOLA.  Just perfect since they were lighter and fluffy.
Its Jambalaya is not as i used to remember it when i first tried it back in 2004. Its bread pudin saved the day
Great crawfish omelet and beignet!

Of course, we went here becuase we saw this place undergo a vast improvement on a certain tv show. It was quite busy mid morning. Nonetheless, the service was friendly and quick, and the food was very good. Many people were taking advantage of the walk up service. The missus and I had a lovely breakfast, and were on our way in good time, but never rushed. Would make it a point to return when we visit NOLA again.
Cute and the food was delicious.

A fantastic little restaurant in the French Quarter that sells calas and grits. Calas is one of the must eat foods in New Orleans as it has a history dating back to the 18th century slaves.  The food is great and the atmosphere exceptional. I’ll be back!
Great food, great selections,  atmosphere was delightful and very reasonable prices.  Would love to go back.
Good food, treated me and my family like family. Too bad they closed down.
We tried to go last Sunday but they were closed down with health department papers posted outside. Too bad. They looked really good! Hopefully they can clean up and reopen soon.

I read the reviews and wanted to try this place. I walked over from my hotel to find they are shut down witha notice on the door. They failed some health and safety inspections and are no longer open. The doors are chained shut.
Great coffee and breakfast
One of my favorites in New Orleans, not crazy busy, great job, and great name. I visit every time I'm in town.
Gordon Ramsay did this place some justice. Great breakfast!
We have been there a couple of times and love it.  Food is great and service was good.
I just watched the show...what happened?  Why did you close?  If staff was an issue why didn’t you replace them?!

Any complaints could stem from lack of decorum...say "hello, we are delighted to be back to New Orleans finest cafe!" with a modicum of energy to whoever shows up first...I gurantee you will get better service. = )

Didn't get served. Waiter ignored us. Served people that came in after us, twice. Never even got our drink order after waiting 20 minutes. Pretentious little joint, prob good food, too bad we weren't cool enough to get served.

This is a little known place on St. Peter to the tourists, but locals like me will not complain.  The people working there have been there for decades and are as sweet and as New Orleans as you can get.  It has an old New Orleans feel to it; you'll be getting a real authentic experience here.
We had the Crab cake Jonathon. It was amazingly delicious! Highly recommended! It's small inside but its quaint and cute!
Our waitress was amazing, the food was stupendous! My first breakfast in New Orleans and I couldn't ask for anything better. Will definitely be back!
Really great restaurant!  The lost bread was ridiculously good!
Good food. Great customer service! Definitely would go back again when in NOLA.
Nice place for breakfast but not such good service
Excellent service and good Cajun food
Great atmosphere, good bloodie!
Just been to this place got 2 eggs 2 slice of bacon and a cup of tea $20!  Each  $40 !!! Unbelievable bad value won't be back!!

Absolutely loved this place. We got in and out quickly even though it was busy and I absolutely loved my server (Wilhelmina?) We asked her to be our new grandmother. The biscuits and gravy were a slam dunk and I'm very picky about that dish. Definitely worth a visit.

The waiter was very friendly and helpful.  Small place off Bourbon street.  Had the crab cake Jonathan ( eggs Benedict with a crab cake instead of ham)  it was very good.   Also the grits here are great.  Love their Coffee too!  HIGHLY RECOMMEND
Great food, Mimosa's are on point and the waitstaff were extremely friendly!  A must to visit!
Why are people eating here???
Super friendly staff, traditional food you'll be hard pressed to find anywhere else. Delicious, and a great view of several small parades while I lingered over coffee.
We always make a point to get some of there bread pudding. Delicious!
Best breakfast I ever had. Grits were on point and the buttermilk chicken biscuits stole the show!!!!
I love this place!  The waitress make this a multiple visit ever time we go to New Orleans! Food is very good too!

Best chicken and andouille sausage gumbo in the quarter area.  Large portions with lots of chicken and sausage.  The beignet bites are amazing as well, served piping hot and loaded with powdered sugar.  Service is great also.
Best gumbo in the quarter! Seafood sampler is amazing!
Great and unique dinning experience. Give it a try.
Amazing food, AWESOME service!!!
You should def eat here! One of my must go to places to eat when I make my yearly trip to NOLA!
Great service. Good food.
Cute little place. I walked by, turned around and had to go in. I had the seafood gumbo. My gumbo game isn't that tight but I can say that I thought it was good.
Absolutely an amazing experience! Food was amazing & couldn't be happier!
Great breakfast joint
Their buttermilk friend chicken benedict is to die for, and the cold brew was amazing! So so so good.

Went here after seeing it on TV. Definitely not worth the trip. We weren't greeted upon arrival and even though there is a sign that says wait to be seated no one came to seat us and the server told up just to be seated anywhere. When we sat down there was no menus on the table except the drink menu. I knew the waitress would be over with the other menu, so I grabbed the drink menu to decide what I wanted to drink. The waitress came back over with the food menus and promptly took the drink menu out of my hand before I could look at it and place it on the opposite side of me. It was extremely rude. I did not say anything because the woman was older. She walked away without another word. I was in disbelief, but I am willing to give any place a second chance. A different waitress came over to the table 2-3 minutes later. She had 1 cup of water (there was 2 of us at the table) and did not greet us. Instead she loudly asked if we wanted anything besides water. We said no and began ordering our food. I had to repeat my order at least three times for the waitress. She did not write anything down just memorized our order which is probably why she had to ask so many times. The food was very basic. Nothing spectacular. Not at all worth what we paid.
Nice breakfast options on the French quarter
Great breakfast

Came for the po boy. We got a crawfish & shrimp. I defiantly love crawfish now. First po boy in NOLA so not sure how it compares but I would so totally eat it again.  Cozy place, cute.  Some waitstaff appeared friendlier than others. A little slow for service but it didn’t bother me.
This place has no service, many came in and left after not being greeted. Our service was terrible and so is bread pudding.
The waitress was very rude and constantly got our orders wrong
Classic New Orleans joint. Great breakfast
Great location, great service, amazing food.
Liked the atmosphere,
Really good service! The waitress was so friendly!

The owner is sooo nice! We had the fried chicken...it came boneless with gravy on top of biscuits.  So good! And their happy hour allowed us to have two Hurricanes for the price of one. Be warned, the sign out front Says "The Pot Gumbo" this is not that resturant--that resturant is down the street and the long line is for Pat O'brien's.
Great food, excellent service and lovely atmosphere!
A bit pricey but food was above average,  Service was great.
Amazing food and wonderful service
Excellent coffee and bread pudding.

Hidden gem of the French Quarter, the ladies that have been serving there for decades are among the sweetest Southern women around.  The food is beyond compare too....breakfast options are great, New Orleans traditional.

We've been coming back here for breakfast time and time again.. It's a favorite stop for us whenever we're in New Orleans. Any breakfast item is great. On this last visit we had the Crab Cakes Benedict and Fried Chicken Benedict. Both were fantastic!!!

The breakfasts served here were fabulous.   We ate here every morning while in New Orleans.  Very convenient from our hotel.   My favorite was the Eggs Jonathan.  JoJo, one of the servers was very kind and delightful.  Would recommend it!  Mid-priced.  $$.

Edit #2: Added automatic gratuity to a party of four. Just noticed reviewing our bill. Not cool. We’ll never be back.  Edit: December 2019. New ownership, new staff. Not close to what it once was. Whole ambience has changed. Shame, used to be our New Orleans must go place. Food is still decent, so if it’s new for you, maybe.  I never felt so good as having Happy Birthday sung to me here. Oh yeah, the food and coffee is great.
Breakfast was delicious, and fast. Was my first time here, will be back for sure
My fav breakfast spot in NOLA!

Ok so I came here recommended by my Google reviewer and I can honestly say no regrets.  The Beinvlle omelette was nothing short of amazing and the service although was very busy was on point. I highly recommend this place as a Global Google guide 10/10

We always have breakfast at The Old Coffee Pot Restaurant. It is tucked away in the quarter and full of New Orleans charm. It was recently "cleaned up" by one of those reality television shows and Chef Gordon Ramsey. Making our annual trek to town for Christmas, and lo and behold, we again find ourselves at their table - this year, brand new tables and chairs. Best grits I've had in quite a while...and good link sausages too. Many of the long-time staffers are still working there - they definitely make the place a signature New Orleans eating spot!
The reviews don't lie, this place has AMAZING food!
Pretty good food. Nice atmosphere.

During my anniversary trip my husband and I have the opportunity to experience breakfast and lunch here, it was amazing.  The staff were friendly and actually remembered us when we return the next day. We will definitely make a return visit the next time we are in  New Orleans.
My meal was so amazing. It’s a perfect spot for a nice, friendly, southern comfort experience. Wow. The waiters were oh so sweet. They even sung to the whole restaurant.
Great place, loved it.
Short walk from Jackson Square, great staff, amazing food.
Love this lol cafe,  food and adult beverages are off the charts!

Great food.  Friendly staff.  The French toast is beyond amazing.  The courtyard is nice and peaceful.  If sitting inside, sit away from windows or may be watching some of the drunk patrons from Pat O'Brians dancing close by them while trying to enjoy meal.

The food was ok here. Not really worth the prices but par for the course in New Orleans. I am giving one star because the service was absolutely abysmal. It took a while to get seated but I didn't mind that. What I did mind was that it took nearly 20 minutes for anyone to even come to the table, and even then it was only to get us waters. The waitress was very rude when she came to take our orders nearly 45 minutes after we sat down. She basically came to the table and grunted "What do you want?" And that was the total extent of her service. Our food came after another half hour. They forgot my friend's side order of eggs. By the time we had finished our meal we had been at the restaurant for nearly an hour and a half. It took another 15 minutes just to spot our waitress and we had to flag her down to get us the check, which took another 15 minutes. At this point I had decided we weren't going to be leaving a nice tip. We get the check and they had added a 10% automatic gratuity! Most restaurants only do that for parties of 6 or more; this restaurant apparently does for parties of 4, and they didn't have this policy anywhere on the menu. We decided not to argue because at the going rate it would probably take another 30 minutes to get the charge removed, which wasn't worth our time. We paid and left having spent over 2 and a half hours at this restaurant.  Waste of time. Horrible service. Will charge you an automatic gratuity they do not deserve. Do not recommend.

I liked my food. My friend was very disappointed. I got the fried chicken with eggs and biscuits and gravy. He got two eggs bacon and hashbrowns. His plate was cold mine was hot so not sure what happened there.
We had the plantation breakfast & crab Benedict. Generous ham slice!
This place is one of the good spots to get an awesome sea food gumbo.  Highly recommend it.
What a great spot for breakfast or lunch.  Friendly staff, very local feel, lots of choices for a great meal you can't get outside of New Orleans.
Cant go wrong with food here!  The chicken benedict, amazing!

Food was good but service was very slow and not as personable as I had hoped.  Nobody was rude and there were no mistakes, but I wasn't impressed and probably won't be back.  There are so many other choices in the French Quarter that I had expected better.
Our service was awesome and the food was delicious!!
Nice place
So glad we found this place. So much we went next day for breakfast and it didn't disappoint.
The best biscuits and gravy and all of New Orleans.  Hard to find but totally worth it

Literally the best breakfast I have ever had. Biscuits with an egg topped with a piece of fried chicken smothered in the most delicious gravy to ever come from any kitchen. Service is out of this world, just mind your P's and Q's, otherwise your gone get-a talk'n to. Go here!!!!
Great place

Food was great but the service is horrible. Even after chef Ramsay make over. After 15 mins of no one acknowledging our table , a waiter tosses a cup of water on the table and leaves. Then she comes back with more water 5 mins later. Advising us 2 put our phones away. I asked for scrambled eggs since i don't like poached eggs and she stated the kitchen to busy for special requests. The only time she was polite was check time. The wait staff does not work together at all. Will not return or recommend this place.
Good breakfast, best part was the sassy waitress from Raleigh NC enjoyable to have conversation with
Love, love, love it here. Wilamina was WONDERFUL. We love you!
Delicious gumbo, homemade corned beef hash, biscuits & gravy, and coffee. Charming, cozy atmosphere, and we loved our waitress.
Awesome food and service
Great , as usual.
What a transformation....🤓
Amazing!
Good breakfast food. Attentive service.
Awesome jumbo...pleasant staff...a good break from the choas on boubon street
You want to experience New Orleans then this is the place.  The most interesting waitress ever.  Cant wait to meet her again
Best Breakfast in NOLA!! Best grits a northerner has ever tasted!!
Interesting atmosphere. A lot of good food to eat. Would go nack to eat again.
Jojo was the best server. Our food was amazing. The Lost Bread had me transported to an ethereal plane. Must try, it was an amazing visit and experience!
Cool place food was just OK but service was good.
There's no place like Home!!
Home made creole breakfast!!! Excellent!!
Nice breakfast selection and prices.  Service was great.
Great food!!!
Super cute, authentic place slightly off the beaten path.  Great service, food and atmosphere.

The food was good and the service was prompt and friendly. The place was clean, which is great, but it looked far more contemporary than I had expected for an old building in New Orleans. It didn't look much different from any new, hipster kind of place you'd find in any suburb.
(Translated by Google) Yummmm  (Original) Yummmm
Waitress did not like the way I mixed my coffee, yankee style. 😃
very good place for breakfast
Corn & crab bisque and seafood gumbo were  awesome!
The best eggs Benedict and grits ever!! Definately the place to go for breakfast/ brunch. And the staff is so nice!
As always perfect. Seafood omelettes are tops!

Excellent! Our waitress, was wonderful. Her brother was the chef.  They are both so personable and wonderful to visit with.  We went twice, in two days, its was so good.  This is excellent seafood gumbo!  You can walk right past it and miss out!  Must go here!

We visited here in September of 2017 as we were driving from Virginia to California . We walked in around 4pm and there were no other customers in the restaurant. We ordered two entrees that we saw on Diners, Drive-In’s, and Dives ... they were good but not great. Considering we were the only customers in the restaurant, the service was a bit slow. The food was good but the entire experience was a bit disappointing.
Yum!! Soul food omelet and a Bloody Mary are a great way to start the day in New Orleans!!
Good tasting breakfast at moderate prices with a New Orleans flare.
Excellent seafood gumbo, good salads and great crabcakes at reasonable prices. Vintage cafe bldg.

Excellent food, and even better service! Everyone in my party tried different things, from the chicken andouille gumbo to the blackened redeye, and we all left full and very happy. The restaurant is cozy and nicely decorated, so it's a nice break from the hustle and bustle of the street. I hope to go back and try the breakfast menu!

Had a great lunch at The Old Coffee Pot. I originally came here to see what it was like after being on Gordon Ramsey’s 24 hours to hell and back show. I was so glad me and my fiancé decided to have lunch here. Our server was friendly and welcoming. We asked him about the show and he was very open to our curiosity. I ordered the chicken and biscuits. Plating was excellent and the chicken tasted delicious. My only critique would be to add more gravy! My fiancé ordered the gumbo and it was his favorite gumbo he tried out of all the the New Orleans restaurants. If you are in New Orleans you HAVE TO TRY Old Coffee Pot. I’m not sure how much of what was shown on TV was true but the food and service we experienced was excellent.
Have the Lost Bread!
Great food
Fabulous breakfast with unique selections.  Would definitely recommend.
Excellent food! Friendly staff, must try!
Food was delicious!
Terrible Service!
I had the fried catfish and jambalaya. My husband ordered the jambalaya by itself. We both enjoyed our meals!

Look, we visited this place on a food tour and came back again. Not only is their food awesome but there prices are even better! Dont be a fool, stop by!!!!! Service is excellent and the atmosphere is relaxed. Perfect place to get away from the crowds. From: walla walla WA
Delicious food, nice outdoor area
The breakfast here is so so good. I dream about the Creole sauce they put on their eggs. It's like nothing else. Mmmmm.

We went for lunch one day and even though it’s in the touristy area of the French Quarters, the food tasted like real southern home cooking! The crab balls and fried chicken with gravy and a biscuit were super delicious! Their drink selection is also ready good. It’s small and was busy when we went for lunch so go early. It’s next to Preservation Hall so go early then hop in line for a show!
Great food service and atmosphere!! Crab and corn cane was delicious!

Was visiting from Baltimore,  Md.. heard so much about the place from the locals.. The service was great.. we had a group of 7 people.. The food was mouth watering.. overall great experience all around ..

To owner... have Never been. But came to read reviews to see how the restraint was holding up since being aired. It seems the reoccurring problem your having, comes down to the service or servers. "Servers are forgetful" hearing constantly...solution have them write down every order. If they do not want to send them home
We had a bug in our drink
great little place for breakfast, good food and friendly service
Food was amazing!! Reasonably priced too

Cajun breakfast with a side of sass.  I had the pleasure of eating here twice while in New Orleans for the weekend.  The food is great, coffee is better.  Take your time while looking over the menu, I missed out on some good food because I ordered too fast.
Love this place! A must stop to any out-of-towners or townees!

My husband and I knew nothing of Gordon Ramsay going to do anything there. I hadn't been to New Orleans in a few years until this past April. Our group of friends (7 of us) went for late breakfast/brunch (no brunch menu, as everything on the menu was available) and the Bloody Mary's were AMAZING!! The Eggs Jonathan was TO DIE FOR.. my husband had the Guy Fieri inspired Triple D and I had a few bites and it was SO FREAKING GOOD! Our waiter was Jonathan and he gave TOP NOTCH SERVICE (again there were 7 of us, with tickets split 3 ways) he gave us exceptional service. The food and service was so damn good, when hubby and I ventured to NOLA for 4th of July weekend, we HAD TO GO BACK!!

A bit pricey, but what a hoot. A real southern experience, the lady in charge was bossing people around left right and centre. Nice clean surroundings, great food. Eggs Benedict on muffin with shrimp on a crab cake with potatoes. Delicious
The food was great, beautiful inside and out. The staff some of the nicest
Best place to eat in New Orleans. Gumbo is just amazing. If you visit, this place is a must.
Delicious food with a great variety of dishes to try.

Seriously. Please don’t go here just because it was featured on a few tv shows or because Gordon Ramsey came to help them out. Seriously! This was terrible in every single way and has vermin!  -The wait took forever and there was hardly anyone there. One server who appeared to be under the influence spent most of her time outside on the sidewalk smoking cigarettes.  -The servers are older, and thus a bit slow, confused and forgetful.  -The food is mediocre at its very best.  Four of us for breakfast took nearly two hours. Our server took our order, dropped it off, got it wrong, and never came back. We went ahead and ate it anyway because we couldn’t seem to find her anywhere. No coffee refills. We waited an additional hour for our check and only got it because we finally went inside to track someone down for it. We were going to just get up and walk away without paying. Incidentally, a man came in while we were there. He sat down and was given a menu. In 25 minutes no one ever came back to take his order. He got up to leave, made a comment to a server on his way out the door telling them they were “rude”, and she couldn’t for the life of her figure out why he was upset. I hollered over “its because you never took his order; he sat there with a menu for 25 minutes” and she just shrugged.  We warned people as we left the building not to bother. A group of guys standing there in the rain nearly 30 minutes insisted on going in just because the place had been featured on TV. However, we succeeded in getting another group of people who had been standing in line for a long time to go somewhere else. A haggard, bedraggled waitress from the establishment who looked like she was under the influence and had a cigarette hanging out of her mouth looked at me really funny and before she could ask me why I suggested the other patrons leave, I stopped her and told her what a horrible experience we had.  Just don’t do it. Mediocre food. High prices. Vermin. The worst service I’ve ever experienced in my life at a restaurant. Who gives a care if the place was visited by Gordon Ramsay because they were having problems? Or because it was featured on television? It’s New Orleans! Half the restaurants here are featured on TV and have famous chefs visit them. The Board of Health should shut this place down. Unacceptable!
I've been coming to this place for over 20 years. I love the service I love the food I love the people

Enjoyed breakfast in this intimate restaurant, but saw they have a beautiful covered and heated outdoor patio hopefully gets opened up for dinner. Fast and frequent service was nice. Ordered an espresso and blueberry mimosa which was delicious. The Eggs Sardou was one of the best Benedict-type dishes I've had including creamed spinach, perfect aoli, and soft runny egg. Grits were meh, should have gotten home fries. Also got the Calas and Grits which were fried rice fritters.. it was interesting and made well, but not something we would order again.

Restaurant is a trap. Cash only (server didn't mention until the end of the meal)  the coffee pot has an ATM outside the restaurant,  with a 5 dollar fee to use. So when you have a party of 8 you're at a potential 40 dollar loss if everyone uses the ATM. Also,  no splitting checks... (Is this 2018?). Food was Meh,  servers were rude.

Awful all around- the staff is super slow and forgetful, the food borderline awful no flavor, presentation outputting and priced not according to quality. Very disappointed the review I've seen doesn't match reality. Not comming back here again

We've always had good experiences here, this time we waited to get seated and then waited for 15 minutes to get menus, another 15 minutes for a server to come by... Once that happened they expedited our service but I was a slow start... Never had that happen before today. And btw they renovated the space ... It's much more country chick with whitewashed barn siding now.
Great Food

Fast, friendly service. Waiter was super helpful explaining the area to us, as we are tourists. Crabcake Jonathon and Eggs Jonathon were spectacular. Coffee was bold and piping hot. Definitely recommend.

Food was ok.  We came here because we saw it on Gordon Ramsay's show, Restaurant Rescue...we figured after that experience it would be nothing short of fantastic.  The whole time we both waited for and we're eating our meal the staff could be heard complaining arguing with each other and using foul language.  At one point one waitress said, "hey we have guests." to the guys in the back but that didn't quiet them down at all.

Breakfast was great. We had creole eggs, grits, pancakes with strawberries, strawberry mimosa, and cold brew coffee. Everything was good and the wait was minimal. The staff were pleasant and efficient. I would recommend this place.

The food was delicious- had the sis soul omelet with grits and the bananas foster French toast. The staff were all amazing and kind. Outside seating was cool and breezy when we went (11am in late August no less). Lastly, prices were good! Definitely recommended!
Our server was amazing and the food as well!! They were really busy but we're very hospitable!!!
The best crab bisque Ive tried. And I travel constantly. Trust you me, its a must!
Great people
Great waiter, maybe the best I've had in the quarter... amazing food and really the best gravy.  Charming and delicious
This place has amazing food and service!
Food was delicious. The servers made us feel like they were serving us in their home while playing the best soul music. These ladies are the soul of the restaurant. Would definitely recommend
Good food and good people:)

We heard great things about this place and it looked adorable. The servers were chatting with each other and there were se rt empty tables. We waited in the doorway for five minutes only being acknowledged when my boyfriend asked a server if we could get seated and we were directed to go back to where we had been. The food may be good but the first impression of the service won’t take me back.
I love the heart and ability to adjust fire!

EXCELLENT!!!! This going to be a 3 Part Review:  Part 1: Service was amazing. Our waitress was so kind and nice she blew our socks off! She is what customer service should be, made us feel like family!  Part 2: The food was Excellent! The Corn & Crab Bisque was yummy. We really enjoyed the food.  Part 3: We went here because it was on the "Gordon Ramsay 24hrs show: and I have to say they kept the decor and is way better! DO NOT ever change. I did notice that the Bar top was cluttered and being used as a serve station instead of a bar (honest review), needs to be cleared off again.  Owner: Need to advertise more, take the fact you were on the show and get some signs out and promote more in the neighborhood :). Get more out of what you age enjoying. I did see that the paint on the ceiling needed a new coat and some minor tweaks that can continue to make this business strive!!!!
Wonderful Gumbo!
Food was pretty good, service was ok
Great food and a very nice environment. Will be back.
My husband's first taste of New Orleans.  A truly memorable experiance.

When I arrived, I waited outside to be seated (as the sign outside instructed me to do) for about 10 minutes. No one greeted us or asked to put our name on the list. I proceeded to walk in to make it known I was there, and was very rudely greeted by an employee who said "can't you see the sign outside? You were supposed to wait to be seated.", and then reluctantly sat us. We then patiently waited for 15 minutes, and not one person checked in on us. Two parties that arrived at least five minutes after us had their order taken before us. Needless to say, I did not spend a dime in there. We got up and left before anyone ever checked in on us. Very disappointing experience. Service was extremely poor.
Great food, and Great service and Entertainment...can't wait to go back.

These negative reviews are bullsh*t saying "they had mice I saw it on TV!!"  Have you never had a bug in your house, your car, have you ever had a mouse in your house in winter trying to find heat and food?  Did you know people have to put chicken wire on the backs of their stoves and ovens to keep rodents out? Or maybe you've had termites or pine roaches, I'm sure you know someone who has.  Did you burn your house or car to the ground?  Did you never use it again?  Hell no.  Yes the toaster was bad, believe that it's gone.  Get a grip, no business is going to be 100% every day of the year.  The whole point is any place could be like that, you don't know, so respect the honesty and integrity that the owner agreed to do this bearinag his faults and fix them.  I have eaten all over the country and will enjoy this place next time the fam hits New Orleans, only a couple hours for us.  I am astounded that the owner didn't walk away, more power to you man, I feel for you I would have shut down too, easy.  I hope you and your kiddos are thriving and you have a fresh start on life.  Yelp bloggers and self named "food critics" are bullsh$t and ruining decent places to get off on a power trip and to make their hollow lives feel important.  Put your damn phone down, give any one a second shot or just don't go back. I'm ashamed to be called a millennial with how we treat others and others lives with technology.  The world doesn't owe us anything and no one needs to know everything you think or fart out of your brain.

I was excited to eat here after Gordon Ramsay revamped the place but was quickly disappointed. The staff was inattentive and drinks were left empty; the worst part, however, was the food.  My shrimp and grits were topped with marinara instead of the bourbon butter sauce as the menu described.   No doubt I will not return.

I read somewhere that if you visit New Orleans that this is the best place for simple breakfast in the French Quarter so I made it a point to stop. I'm not disappointed at all that we did. Certainly a place with a lot of history, the building has a simply perfect outside seating area which thankfully had a near continuous gentle breeze helping to keep the heat of the late morning from ruining our experience. The food was very good in a comfort food sort of way. Scrambled eggs were a little dry, but the poached eggs were perfectly done. Our server was a little rough at first, but once she got a cup of coffee, or 3, in her she warmed right up and was extremely pleasant. As for the best place in the French Quarter, I personally put it second.

Stopped by the Old Coffee Pot this evening after seeing it on Hell's Kitchen last night.  It looked much smaller than on TV.  I was surprised.  My son was so curious to see the place after just watching it on TV.  He wanted to make sure the mouse was removed from the toaster and the kitchen.  Kids!  Anyway, we didn't eat there.  I had a cocktail and my son had a Sprite only.  We were only there to see the rennovations and if they were still in business.  We had a delightful conversation with Chris the new bartenter and a cook and snapped a few pictures of the decor.  Chris was humble, frank, professional and very sociable as a good bartender should be.    The cook was also very polite and friendly and answered all.my son's questions.  We enjoyed our short visit there drinking our refreshments and chatting with Chris.  I cannot speak for the food because we had eaten before our visit.  In my opinion, definitely more rennovations could have been made but due to the time constraints of the location and the production department of Hell's Kitchen I gathered they couldn't do more in the short span of time allocated. Shame.  We didn't see any women staff there thank God because on TV show they seemed to be a big source of the problem.  I hope the owner will finally make a decision to either be all in or out because whatever was going on is still lingering in the air.  It seems like a cool spot to duck in for a while when out and about and it sits direct next door to Pat O'Brian's. Within an hour of leaving my son complained his tummy hurt and we had to stop twice for him to potty and a couple hours later I was in the restroom for a while.  Hmm, maybe the ice cubes.  I didn't expect that.  I wanted to give it at least a 4-star until we both had tummy issues right after leaving.  But it has a lovely alley outside dining/drinking area, is decorated cute and bright and Chris the bartender wasn't there when the show aired but was the best part of our experience.  Thanks again to Chris and the cook.

On a recommendation from a friend, I visited this restaurant to try the Eggs Sardeau. They definitely did not disappoint! Toasted English muffins topped with cream spinach, poached eggs, and hollandaise sauce were delicious! They come with a side of either potatoes or grits. My mom had the corn and crawfish chowder which was also quite tasty although a bit salty. While the food was delicious, the service was among the worst I have experienced in several years. There were 2 servers working who were slow, inefficient, unorganized, and unapologetic. It took about 15 minutes before we were greeted at the door and offered a table. After sitting down, it was another 15 to 20 minutes before anyone even acknowledged our presence at a table. During this time, I watched several tables get up and leave from not being acknowledged and a server get a drink order, make drinks, bring the drinks to the table, and get a food order from a single table while not acknowledging any of the other guests who were waiting at tables nearby.  I have worked as a server, and I know the key to being a good server is being able to multitask, apologize, and be friendly. Unfortunately, these servers missed the first 2 by far. The male server changed his hair several times while we ate. It is amazing to me that he had time to put his hair into a ponytail and then take it back down multiple times yet there were tables who were waiting for service.

It was ok they served an overdone poached egg tried three times to get the attention of server but after 5 minutes they finally came over . They reheated the fried chicken and gave me a new Poached egg. Was not a happy camper !
